## ✖ dplyr::lag()    masks stats::lag()
bison <- read_csv('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/brendanrbrown/brendanrbrown.github.io/master/smallbison.csv')
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   latitude = col_double(),
##   longitude = col_double(),
##   dtime = col_double()
## )
K <- 4
set.seed(1305)
m <- kmeans(data.matrix(bison), centers = K)
bison <- mutate(bison, cluster = factor(m$cluster))
bison2 <- read_csv('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/brendanrbrown/brendanrbrown.github.io/master/smallbison.csv')
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   latitude = col_double(),
##   longitude = col_double(),
##   dtime = col_double()
## )
K <- 6
set.seed(1865202)
m <- kmeans(data.matrix(bison2), centers = K)
bison2 <- mutate(bison2, cluster = factor(m$cluster))
group_by(bison, cluster) %>% 
  summarise(n = n(), latitude = mean(latitude),
            longitude = mean(longitude),
            dtime = mean(dtime))
## # A tibble: 4 x 5
##   cluster     n latitude longitude  dtime
##   <fct>   <int>    <dbl>     <dbl>  <dbl>
## 1 1       30631     36.0     -79.1  3241.
## 2 2        7115     36.0     -79.1 18635.
## 3 3       13306     35.9     -79.1 10959.
## 4 4       12207     36.0     -79.1  6576.
cent <- as_tibble(m$centers) %>% mutate(cluster = factor(1:K))
ggplot(bison, aes(x = latitude, y = longitude, color = cluster)) + geom_point(size = 3, alpha = .7) +
  theme_bw() + scale_color_brewer(type = "qual", palette = "Set1") +
  geom_point(data = cent, size = 10, shape = 13)

group_by(bison2, cluster) %>% 
  summarise(n = n(), latitude = mean(latitude),
            longitude = mean(longitude),
            dtime = mean(dtime))
## # A tibble: 6 x 5
##   cluster     n latitude longitude  dtime
##   <fct>   <int>    <dbl>     <dbl>  <dbl>
## 1 1        7125     36.0     -79.0  7277.

## 4 4        6006     36.0     -79.1  5543.
## 5 5       12389     36.0     -79.1  3900.
## 6 6       17430     36.0     -79.1  2702.
bison <- read_csv('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/brendanrbrown/brendanrbrown.github.io/master/smallbison.csv')
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   latitude = col_double(),
##   longitude = col_double(),
##   dtime = col_double()
## )
K <- 4
set.seed(1305)
bison = mutate(bison, latitude = scale(latitude)[,1])
bison = mutate(bison, longitude = scale(longitude)[,1])
bison = mutate(bison, dtime = scale(dtime)[,1])
m <- kmeans(data.matrix(bison), centers = K)
bison <- mutate(bison, cluster = factor(m$cluster))
group_by(bison, cluster) %>% 
  summarise(n = n(), latitude = mean(latitude),
            longitude = mean(longitude),
            dtime = mean(dtime))
## # A tibble: 4 x 5
##   cluster     n latitude longitude  dtime
##   <fct>   <int>    <dbl>     <dbl>  <dbl>
## 1 1       29192   -0.528     0.214 -0.519
## 2 2       14564   -0.597     0.466  1.05 
## 3 3       14156    0.970    -1.42   0.250
## 4 4        5347    1.94      1.32  -0.675
cent <- as_tibble(m$centers) %>% mutate(cluster = factor(1:K))
ggplot(bison, aes(x = latitude, y = longitude, color = cluster)) + geom_point(size = 3, alpha = .7) +
  theme_bw() + scale_color_brewer(type = "qual", palette = "Set1") +
  geom_point(data = cent, size = 10, shape = 13)
